ASTHMA ATTACKS DURING WINTER Asthma and respiratory conditions are overwhelming hospitals. In England, over 868,000 emergency hospital admissions for respiratory diseases like asthma and COPD were recorded in 2023-24, accounting for one in eight unplanned admissions. Cold weather and infections significantly increase admissions due to lung inflammation and exacerbations of conditions like asthma. Many of these admissions are avoidable. Poor management of asthma and COPD, including lack of flu vaccinations, contributes to these figures. Only 10% of lung patients in 2023 received all five essential treatments, including smoking cessation, vaccinations, and medication reviews—a stark drop from 26% in 2021. Respiratory conditions are the leading cause of emergency admissions, outpacing injuries and heart issues, and straining hospital resources, especially in winter. Poorer individuals are twice as likely to be hospitalized for breathing issues compared to wealthier counterparts. #asthma #copd #breathing  #AsthmaAwareness #WinterHealthTips #BreathingEasy #COPDAwareness #LungHealthMatters #StayOutOfHospital #ColdWeatherCare #FluSeasonTips #FightForBreath #HealthyLungs #nhs #askyourpharmacist #medication #fyp #doctor #nurse #pharmacistsoftiktok #pharmacy  #pharmacist  How can I prevent asthma attacks during winter?
